### Description

Based on my understanding, it seems that Angular currently doesn't offer a means to inject a unique instance into a service.

If I want to inject a unique instance similar to the following code, how can I achieve that when using an angular standalone component?

```
@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root'
})
export class MyService {
  constructor(private uniqueInstanceA: UniqueInstance, private uniqueInstanceB: UniqueInstance) {
      uniqueInstanceA.setUrl("/api/abc");
      uniqueInstanceB.setUrl("/api/def");
  }
```

```
@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'any'
})
export class UniqueInstance{
  url: string = "";
  constructor(private http: HttpClient) { } 
  
  setUrl(url:string) {
      this.url = url;
  } 
```
 


### Proposed solution

Is it possible to use the 'any' option in the 'providedIn' property again?

